{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
Recorded since 1929, from {{affix|en|recess|-ion}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|recessus||a going back, retreat}}, from {{m|la|recessum}}, the past participle of {{m|la|recedere||to recede}}, from {{m|la|re-||back}} + {{m|la|cedere||to go}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act or an instance of [[receding]] or withdrawing.
#* Jeremy Taylor
#*: Mercy may rejoice upon the '''recessions''' of justice.
# A period of reduced [[economic]] [[activity]]
#: ''Statisticians often define a '''recession''' as negative, real GDP growth during two consecutive [[quarter]]s.
# The [[ceremonial]] [[file out|filing out]] of [[clergy]] and/or choir at the end of a church service.

